  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong>&nbsp;rice</strong>, 350ml<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;[700ml]</span>&nbsp;water to a pot with a lid over a high heat and bring to the boil</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-in-a-hurry/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>chicken</strong>&nbsp;into thin strips and coat them thoroughly in the <strong>cornflour</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a large drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once&nbsp;hot, add the <strong>chicken</strong> and cook for 2 min on each side, or until browned</p>\r\n<p>Once browned, transfer the chicken&nbsp;to a plate and keep the pan for the next step</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-in-a-hurry/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Return&nbsp;the pan to a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once&nbsp;hot, add the <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>curry powder</strong> and <strong>garlic </strong>and cook&nbsp;for 30 sec</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-in-a-hurry/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>chicken</strong> to the pan, crumble in the <strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong>and add 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]&nbsp;</span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat to medium-low, and cook, covered,&nbsp;for 5 min, or until the chicken is cooked through</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-in-a-hurry/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop&nbsp;the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Trim and slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Dice the <strong>tomatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-in-a-hurry/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Fluff the rice and add the <strong>coriander</strong>, <strong>spring onion</strong> and<strong> tomato</strong></p>\r\n<p>Season with <strong>pepper</strong> and mix gently</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-in-a-hurry/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has cooked and the sauce has reduced down, remove the chicken pan from the heat and stir in the <strong>yoghurt</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-in-a-hurry/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the curry over the rice</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
